cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper discusses the use of procedural content generation (PCG) in video games and its application to machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the use of PCG to create open-ended learning environments and combat overfitting in supervised and reinforcement learning tasks. The paper also touches on graphics and rendering (cs.GR) in the context of generating game levels, as well as computer vision (cs.CV) in the context of OpenAI's robot arm learning to manipulate objects. Finally, the paper briefly mentions the use of PCG to create better benchmarks (cs.SD, Software Engineering), which could ultimately spur the development of better learning algorithms.
